<p>Photo taken on Oct. 26, 2020 shows that vendors were buying newly caught sea cucumbers at Tianhai Bay of Hushan Town, Rongcheng City, east China's Shandong Province. In recent years, Rongcheng has vigorously developed aquaculture for natural multiplication of seedlings placed on the seabed. At present, sea cucumber aquaculture has become one of the pillar industries for increasing the efficiency of the local fishery and the income of the local fishermen. (Lin Haizhen/Guangming Picture)</p>
